  line `21. Officers and other employees of Authority.`
  line `22. Transfer of assets, liabilities of Authority.`
  line `23. Powers and functions of Authority.`
  line `23A. Power of Authority to issue directions.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `G RANTS, A CCOUNTSAND A UDITAND A NNUAL R EPORT`
  line `24. Grants by Central Government.`
  line `25. Fund.`
  line `26. Accounts and audit.`
  line `27. Returns and annual report, etc.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `P ROTECTIONOF I NFORMATION`
  line `28. Security and confidentiality of information.`
  line `29. Restriction on sharing information.`
  line `30. Biometric information deemed to be sensitive personal information.`
  line `31. Alteration of demographic information or biometric information.`
  line `32. Access to own information and records of requests for authentication.`
  line `33. Disclosure of information in certain ca ses.`
  line `CHAPTER VIA`
  line `C IVIL PENALTIES`
  line `33A. Penalty for failure to comply with provisions of this Act, rules, regulations and`
  line directions.
  line `33B. Power to adjudicate.`
  line `33C. Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `33D. Procedure and powers of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `33E. Appeal to Supreme Court of India.`
  line `33F. Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
