  string
  line 3
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `O FFENCESAND P ENALTIES`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `34. Penalty for impersonation at time of enrolment.`
  line `35. Penalty for impersonation of Aadhaar number holder by changing demographic information or`
  line `biometric information.`
  line `36. Penalty for impersonation.`
  line `37. Penalty for disclosing identity information.`
  line `38. Penalty for unauthorised access to the Central Identities Data Repository.`
  line `39. Penalty for tampering with data in Central Identities Data Repository.`
  line `40. Penalty for unauthorised use by requesting entity or offline verification - seeking entity.`
  line `41. Penalty for non - compliance with intimation requirements.`
  line `42. General penalty.`
  line `43. Offences by companies.`
  line `44. Act to app ly for offence or contravention committed outside India.`
  line `45. Power to investigate offences.`
  line `46. Penalties not to interfere with other punishments.`
  line `47. Cognizance of offences.`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `48. Power of Central Government to supersede Authority.`
  line `49. Members, officers, etc., to be public servants.`
  line `50. Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  line `50A. Exemption from tax on income.`
  line `51. Delegation.`
  line `52. Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  line `53. Power of Central Government to make ru les.`
  line `54. Power of Authority to make regulations.`
  line `55. Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  line `56. Application of other laws not barred.`
  line `57. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `58. Power to remove difficulties.`
  line `59. Savings.`
