obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE AADHAAR (TARGETED DELIVERY OF FINANCIAL AND OTHER SUBSIDIES,`
  line `BENEFITS AND SERVICES) ACT, 2016`
  line `A CT N O. 18 OF 2016`
  line `[25 th March, 2016. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for, as a good governance, efficient, transparent, and targeted delivery of`
  line `subsidies, benefits and services, the expenditure for which is incurr ed from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India, 1 [ or the Consolidated Fund of the State ] to individuals residing in India`
  line `through assigning of unique identity numbers to such individuals and for matters connected`
  line `therewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Sixty - seventh Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Aadhaar (Targeted`
  line `Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall extend to the whole of India 2 *** and save as otherwise provided in this Act, it shall also`
  line `apply to any offence or contravention thereunder committed outside India by any person.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may, be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the commencement of that provision.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `4 [ ( a ) “ Aadhaar number ” means an identification number issued to an individual under sub - section`
  line `( 3 ) of section 3, and includes any alternative virtual identity generated under sub - section ( 4 ) of that`
  line `section; ]`
  line `5 [( aa ) “ Aadhaar ecosystem ” includes enrolling agencies, Registrars, requesting entities, offline`
  line `verification - seeking entities and any other entity or group of entities as may b e specified by`
  line regulations;]
  line `( b ) “ Aadhaar number holder ” means an individual who has been issued an Aadhaar number under`
  line `this Act;`
  line `4 [ ( ba ) “ Adjudicating Officer ” means an Adjudicating Officer appointed under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 33B;`
  line `( bb ) “ Appellate Tribunal ” means the Appellate Tribunal referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section`
  line 33C;]
  line `( c ) “ authentication ” means the process by which the Aadhaar number alongwith demographic`
  line `information or biometric information of an individual is submitted to the Central Identities Data`
  line `Repository for its verification and such Repository verifies the correctness, or the lack thereof, on the`
  line `basis of information available with it;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. The w ords “except the State of Jammu and Kashmir” omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 2019).`
  line `3. 12th September, 2016 — S ections 1 to 10, 24 to 47, vide notification No. S.O. 2927 (E), dated 12th September, 2016 see`
  line `Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part II, s. 3 ( ii ).`
  line `12th July, 2016 — Section s 11 to 20, 22 and 23, 48 to 59, vide notification No. S.O. 2357 (E), dated 12 the July 2016, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, s. 3 ( ii ).`
  line `25 th July, 2019 — Section s1 to 30, vide notification No. S.O. 2649 (E), dated 25th July, 2019 see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, s. 3 ( ii ).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s, 3, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 3, ibid, (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
