  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( d ) “ authentication record ” means the record of the time of authentication and identity of the`
  line `requesting entity and the response provided by the Authority thereto;`
  line `( e ) “ Authority ” means the Unique Identification Authority of India established under sub - s ection`
  line `( 1 ) of section 11;`
  line `( f ) “ benefit ” means any advantage, gift, reward, relief, or payment, in cash or kind, provided to an`
  line `individual or a group of individuals and includes such other benefits as may be notified by the Central`
  line Government;
  line `( g ) “ biometri c information ” means photograph, finger print, Iris scan, or such other biological`
  line `attributes of an individual as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( h ) “ Central Identities Data Repository ” means a centralised database in one or more locations`
  line `containing all Aadhaar numbers issued to Aadhaar number holders along with the corresponding`
  line `demographic information and biometric information of such individuals and other information related`
  line thereto;
  line `( i ) “ Chairperson ” m eans the Chairperson of the Authority appointed under section 12;`
  line `1 [( ia ) “ child ” means a person who has not completed eighteen years of age;]`
  line `( j ) “ core biometric information ” means finger print, Iris scan, or such other biological attribute of`
  line `an individua l as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( k ) “ demographic information ” includes information relating to the name, date of birth, address`
  line `and other relevant information of an individual, as may be specified by regulations for the purpose of`
  line `issuing an Aadhaar number, but shall not include race, religion, caste, tribe, ethnicity, language,`
  line `records of entitlement, income or medical history;`
  line `( l ) “ enrolling agency ” means an agency appointed by the Authority or a Registrar, as the case`
  line `may be, fo r collecting demographic and biometric information of individuals under this Act;`
  line `( m ) “ enrolment ” means the process, as may be specified by regulations, to collect demographic`
  line `and biometric information from individuals by the enrolling agencies for the pur pose of issuing`
  line `Aadhaar numbers to such individuals under this Act;`
  line `( n ) “ identity information ” in respect of an individual, includes his Aadhaar number, his biometric`
  line `information and his demographic information;`
  line `( o ) “ Member ” includes the Chairperson and Me mber of the Authority appointed under section 12;`
  line `( p ) “ notification ” means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `“ notified ” with its cognate meanings and grammatical variations shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `1 [ ( pa ) “ offline verification ” means the process of verifying the identity of the Aadhaar number`
  line `holder without authentication, through such offline modes as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( pb ) “ offline verification - seeking entity ” means any entity desirous of undertaking offline`
  line `verification of an Aadhaar number holder;]`
  line `( q ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line `( r ) “ records of entitlement ” means records of benefits, subsidies or services provided to, or`
  line `availed b y, any individual under any programme;`
  line `( s ) “ Registrar ” means any entity authorised or recognised by the Authority for the purpose of`
  line `enrolling individuals under this Act;`
  line `( t ) “ regulations ” means the regulations made by the Authority under this Act;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 3 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( u ) “ re questing entity ” means an agency or person that submits the Aadhaar number, and`
  line `demographic information or biometric information, of an individual to the Central Identities Data`
  line `Repository for authentication;`
  line `( v ) “ resident ” means an individual who has resi ded in India for a period or periods amounting in`
  line `all to one hundred and eighty - two days or more in the twelve months immediately preceding the date`
  line `of application for enrolment;`
  line `( w ) “ service ” means any provision, facility, utility or any other assistance provided in any form to`
  line `an individual or a group of individuals and includes such other services as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line `( x ) “ subsidy ” means any form of aid, support, grant, subvention, or appropriation, in cash or kind,`
  line `to an individ ual or a group of individuals and includes such other subsidies as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `E NROLMENT`
  line `3. Aadhaar number. — ( 1 ) Every resident shall be entitled to obtain an Aadhaar number by`
  line `submitting his demographic information and biometric information by undergoing the process of`
  line `enrolment:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, from time to time, notify such other category of`
  line `individuals who may be entitled to obtain an Aadhaar number.`
  line `( 2 ) The enrolling agency shall, at th e time of enrolment, inform the individual undergoing enrolment`
  line `of the following details in such manner as may be specified by regulations, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the manner in which the information shall be used;`
  line `( b ) the nature of recipients with whom the informati on is intended to be shared during`
  line `authentication; and`
  line `( c ) the existence of a right to access information, the procedure for making requests for such`
  line `access, and details of the person or department in - charge to whom such requests can be made.`
  line `( 3 ) On receipt of the demographic information and biometric information under sub - section ( 1 ), the`
  line `Authority shall, after verifying the information, in such manner as may be specified by regulations, issue`
  line `an Aad haar number to such individual.`
  line `1 [( 4 ) The Aadhaar n umber issued to an individual under sub - section ( 3 ) shall be a twelve - digit`
  line `identification number and any alternative virtual identity as an alternative to the actual Aadhaar number`
  line `of an individual that shall be generated by the Authority in such manner a s may be specified by`
  line regulations.]
  line `2 [ 3A. Aadhaar number of children. — ( 1 ) The enrolling agency shall, at the time of enrolment of a`
  line `child, seek the consent of the parent or guardian of the child, and inform the parent or guardian, the`
  line `details specified under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3.`
  line `( 2 ) A child who is an Aadhaar number holder may, within a period of six months of attaining the`
  line `eighteen years of age, make an application to the Authority for cancellation of his Aadhaar number, in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations and the Authority shall cancel his Aadhaar number.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything in section 7, a child shall not be denied any subsidy, benefit or service`
  line `under that section in case of failure to establish his identity by undergoin g authentication, or furnishing`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid, (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `proof of possession of Aadhaar number, or in the case of a child to whom no Aadhaar number has been`
  line `assigned, producing an application for enrolment.]`
  line `4. Properties of Aadhaar number. — ( 1 ) An Aadhaar number, issued to an indi vidual shall not be re -`
  line `assigned to any other individual.`
  line `( 2 ) An Aadhaar number shall be a random number and bear no relation to the attributes or identity of`
  line `the Aadhaar number holder.`
  line `1 [(3) Every Aadhaar number holder to establish his identity, may voluntarily use his Aadhaar number`
  line `in physical or electronic form by way of authentication or offline verification, or in such other form as`
  line `may be notified, in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, voluntary use of the Aadhaar number by way of`
  line `authentication means the use of such Aadhaar number only with the informed consent of the Aadhaar`
  line `number holder.`
  line `( 4 ) An entity may be allowed to perform authentication, if the Authority is satisfied that the r equesting`
  line `entity is —`
  line `( a ) compliant with such standards of privacy and security as may be specified by regulations; and`
  line `( b ) ( i ) permitted to offer authentication services under the provisions of any other law made by`
  line `Parliament; or`
  line `( ii ) seeking authenticat ion for such purpose, as the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Authority, and in the interest of State, may prescribe.`
  line `( 5 ) The Authority may, by regulations, decide whether a requesting entity shall be permitted the use of`
  line `the actual Aadhaar numb er during authentication or only an alternative virtual identity.`
  line `( 6 ) Every requesting entity to whom an authentication request is made by an Aadhaar number holder`
  line `under sub - section ( 3 ) shall inform to the Aadhaar number holder of alternate and viable mean s of`
  line `identification and shall not deny any service to him for refusing to, or being unable to, undergo`
  line authentication.
  line `( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions, mandatory authentication of an`
  line `Aadhaar number holder for the provisio n of any service shall take place if such authentication is required`
  line `by a law made by Parliament.]`
  line `5. Special measures for issuance of Aadhaar number to certain category of persons. — The`
  line `Authority shall take special measures to issue Aadhaar number to women, children, senior citizens,`
  line `persons with disability, unskilled and unorganised workers, nomadic tribes or to such other persons who`
  line `do not have any permanent dwelling house and such other categories of individuals as m ay be specified`
  line `by regulations.`
  line `6. Update of certain information. — The Authority may require Aadhaar number holders to update`
  line `their demographic information and biometric information, from time to time, in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by regulations, so as to ensure continued accuracy of their information in the Central Identities`
  line `Data Repository.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 6, for Sub - section (3) (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
