  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `A UTHENTICATION`
  line `7. Proof of Aadhaar number necessary for receipt of certain subsidies, benefits and services,`
  line `et c. — The Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `establishing identity of an individual as a condition for receipt of a subsidy, benefit or service for which`
  line `the expenditure is incurred from, or the receipt the refrom forms part of, the Consolidated Fund of India,`
  line `1 [or the Consolidated Fund of State] require that such individual undergo authentication, or furnish proof`
  line `of possession of Aadhaar number or in the case of an individual to whom no Aadhaar number has been`
  line `assigned, such individual makes an application for enrolment:`
  line `Provided that if an Aadh aar number is not assigned to an individual, the individual shall be offered`
  line `alternate and viable means of identification for delivery of the subsidy, benefit or service.`
  line `8. Authentication of Aadhaar number. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall perform authentication o f the`
  line `Aadhaar number of an Aadhaar number holder submitted by any requesting entity, in relation to his`
  line `biometric information or demographic information, subject to such conditions and on payment of such`
  line `fees and in such manner as may be specified by regul ations.`
  line `( 2 ) A requesting entity shall —`
  line `( a ) unless otherwise provided in this Act, obtain the consent of an individual 2 [or in the case of a`
  line `child obtain the consent of his parent or guardian] before collecting his identity information for the`
  line `purposes of authentication in such manner as may be specified by regulations; and`
  line `( b ) ensure that the identity information of an individual is only used for submission to the Central`
  line `Identities Data Repository for authentication.`
  line `2 [Provided that the requesting entity shall, in case of failure to authenticate due to illness, injury`
  line `or infirmity owing to old age or otherwise or any technical or other reasons, provide such alternate and`
  line `viable means of identification of the individual, as may be specified by regulations.]`
  line `( 3 ) A requesting entity shall inform, in such manner as may be specified by regulations, the individual`
  line `submitting his identity information for authentication 2 [or in the case of a child, his parent or guardian],`
  line `the following details with respect to authentication, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the nature of information that may be shared upon authentication;`
  line `( b ) the uses to which the information received during authentication may be put by the requesting`
  line `entity; and`
  line `( c ) alternatives to submission of identity information to the requesting entity.`
  line `( 4 ) The Authority shall respond to an authentication query with a positive, negative or any other`
  line `appropriate response sharing such identity information excluding any core biometric informati on.`
  line `3 [ 8A. Offline verification of Aadhaar number. — ( 1 ) Every offline verification of an Aadhaar`
  line `number holder shall be performed in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 2 ) Every offline verification - seeking entity shall, —`
  line `( a ) before performing offline verification, obtain the consent of an individual, or in the case of a`
  line `child, his parent or guardian, in such manner as may be specified by regulations; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 7 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid, (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid, (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `( b ) ensure that the demographic information or any other information collected from the in dividual`
  line `for offline verification is only used for the purpose of such verification.`
  line `( 3 ) An offline verification - seeking entity shall inform the individual undergoing offline verification, or`
  line `in the case of a child, his parent or guardian, the following de tails with respect to offline verification, in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the nature of information that may be shared upon offline verification;`
  line `( b ) the uses to which the information received during offline verification m ay be put by the offline`
  line `verification - seeking entity; and`
  line `( c ) alternatives to submission of information requested for, if any.`
  line `( 4 ) No offline verification - seeking entity shall —`
  line `( a ) subject an Aadhaar number holder to authentication;`
  line `( b ) collect, use, or st ore an Aadhaar number or biometric information of any individual for any`
  line purpose;
  line `( c ) take any action contrary to any obligation on it as may be specified by regulations.]`
  line `9. Aadhaar number not evidence of citizenship or domicile, etc. — The Aadhaar number or the`
  line `authentication thereof shall not, by itself, confer any right of, or be proof of, citizenship or domicile in`
  line `respect of an Aadhaar number holder.`
  line `10. Central Identities Data Repository. — The Authority may engage one or more entitie s to`
  line `establish and maintain the Central Identities Data Repository and to perform any other functions as may`
  line `be specified by regulations.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `U NIQUE I DENTIFICATION A UTHORITYOF I NIDA`
  line `11. Establishment of Authority. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall, by notification, establish an`
  line `Authority to be known as the Unique Identification Authority of India to be responsible for the processes`
  line `of enrolment and authentication and perform such other functions assigned to it under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line `( 3 ) The head office of the Authority shall be in New Delhi.`
  line `( 4 ) The Authority may, with the prior approval of the Central Government, establish its offices at`
  line `other places in India.`
  line `12. Composition of Authority. — The Authority shall consist of a Chairperson, appointed on part -`
  line `time or full - time basis, two part - time Members, and the chief executive officer who shall be Member -`
  line `Secretary of the Authority, to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line `13. Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and Members of Authority. — The Chairperson`
  line `and Members of the Authority shall be persons of ability and integrity having experience and knowledge`
  line `of at least ten years in matters relating to technology, governance, law, development, economics, finance,`
  line `man agement, pu blic affairs or administration.`
  line `14. Term of office and other conditions of service of Chairperson and Members. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Chairperson and the Members appointed under this Act shall hold office for a term of three years from the`
  line `date on which they a ssume office and shall be eligible for re - appointment:`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as the Chairperson or Member after he has attained the age`
  line `of sixty - five years.`
  line `( 2 ) The Chairperson and every Member shall, before entering office, make and subscribe to, an oath`
  line `of office and of secrecy, in such form and in such manner and before such Authority as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), the Chairperson or Member may —`
  line `( a ) relinquish his office, by giving i n writing to the Central Government, a notice of not less than`
  line `thirty days; or`
  line `( b ) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 15.`
  line `( 4 ) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and allowances or remuneration payable to part - time Members shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `15. Removal of Chairperson and Members. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may remove from`
  line `office, the Chairperson, or a Member, who —`
  line `( a ) is, or at any tim e has been adjudged as insolvent;`
  line `( b ) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as the Chairperson or, as the case may`
  line `be, a Member;`
  line `( c ) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line `( d ) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `the Chairperson or, as the case may be, a Member; or`
  line `( e ) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused his position as to render his`
  line `continu ance in office detrimental to the public interest.`
  line `( 2 ) The Chairperson or a Member shall not be removed under clause ( b ), clause ( d ) or clause ( e ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) unless he has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `16. Restrictions on Chairperson or Members on employment after cessation of office. — The`
  line `Chairperson or a Member on ceasing to hold office for any reason, shall not, without previous approval of`
  line `the Central Government, —`
  line `( a ) accept any employment in, or be conne cted with the management of any organisation,`
  line `company or any other entity which has been associated with any work done or contracted out by the`
  line `Authority, whether directly or indirectly, during his tenure as Chairperson or Member, as the case`
  line `may be, for a period of three years from the date on which he ceases to hold office:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any employment under the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or local authority or in any statutory authority or any corporation`
  line `established by or under any Central, State or provincial Act or a Government Company, as defined in`
  line `clause ( 45 ) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line `( b ) act, for or on behalf of any person or organisation in connection with any specific proceeding`
  line `or transaction or negotiation or a case to which the Authority is a party and with respect to which the`
  line `Chairperson or such Member had, before cessation of off ice, acted for or provided advice to, the`
  line Authority;
  line `( c ) give advice to any person using information which was obtained in his capacity as the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member and being unavailable to or not being able to be made available to the`
  line `public; or`
  line `( d ) ent er, for a period of three years from his last day in office, into a contract of service with,`
  line `accept an appointment to a board of directors of, or accept an offer of employment with, an entity`
  line `with which he had direct and significant official deal ings duri ng his term of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `17. Functions of Chairperson. — The Chairperson shall preside over the meetings of the Authority,`
  line `and without prejudice to any provision of this Act, exercise and discharge such other powers and`
  line `functions of the Authority as may be pre scribed.`
  line `18. Chief executive officer. — ( 1 ) There shall be a chief executive officer of the Authority, not below`
  line `the rank of Additional Secretary to the Government of India, to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The chief executive officer shall be the legal representative of the Authority and shall be`
  line `responsible for —`
  line `( a ) the day - to - day administration of the Authority;`
  line `( b ) implementing the work programmes and decisions adopted by the Authority;`
  line `( c ) drawing up of proposal for the Authority' s decisions and work programmes;`
  line `( d ) the preparation of the statement of revenue and expenditure and the execution of the budget of`
  line `the Authority; and`
  line `( e ) performing such other functions, or exercising such other powers, as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line `( 3 ) Every year, the chief executive officer shall submit to the Authority for approval —`
  line `( a ) a general report covering all the activities of the Authority in the previous year;`
  line `( b ) programmes of work;`
  line `( c ) the annual accounts for the previous year; and`
  line `( d ) the budget for the coming year.`
  line `( 4 ) The chief executive officer shall have administrative control over the officers and ot her employees`
  line `of the Authority.`
  line `19. Meetings of Authority. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `suc h rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, including quorum at such`
  line `meetings, as may be specified by regulations.`
  line `( 2 ) The Chairperson, or, if for any reason, he is unable to attend a meeting of the Authority, the senior`
  line `most Member shall preside over the meetings of the Authority.`
  line `( 3 ) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes by the Members present and voting and in the event of anequality of votes, the Chairpe rson or in`
  line `his absence the presiding Member shall have a casting vote.`
  line `( 4 ) All decisions of the Authority shall be signed by the Chairperson or any other Member or the`
  line `Member - Secretary authorised by the Authority in this behalf.`
  line `( 5 ) If any Member, who is a director of a company and who as such director, has any direct or`
  line `indirect pecuniary interest in any manner coming up for consideration at a meeting of the Authority, he`
  line `shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his knowledge, d isclose the nature of`
  line `his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be recorded in the proceedings of the Authority, and`
  line `the Member shall not take part in any deliberation or decision of the Authori ty with respect to that matter.`
  line `20. Vacancies, et c., not to invalidate proceedings of Authority. — No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of —`
  line `( a ) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority;`
  line `( b ) any defect in the appointment of a person as Chairperson or Member of the Authority; or`
  line `( c ) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not af fecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `1 [ 21. Officers and other employees of Authority. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall appoint such officers and`
  line `employees as may be required for the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and employees of the Authority shall be such as may be specified by regulations.]`
  line `22. Tra nsfer of assets, liabilities of Authority. — On and from the establishment of the Authority —`
  line `( a ) all the assets and liabilities of the Unique Identification Authority of India, established vide`
  line `notification of the Government of India in the Planning Commission number A - 43011/02/2009 -`
  line `Admin. I, dated the 28th January, 2009, shall stand transferred to, and vested in, the Authority.`
  line `Explanation. — The assets of such Unique Identification Authority of India shall be deemed to include`
  line `all rights and powers, and all properties, whether movable or immovable, including, in particular, cash`
  line `balances, deposits and all other interests and rights in, or arising out of, such properties as may be in the`
  line `possessio n of such Unique Identification Authority of India and all books of account and other documents`
  line `relating to the same; and liabilities shall be deemed to include all debts, liabilities and obligations of`
  line `whatever kind;`
  line `( b ) without prejudice to the provision s of clause ( a ), all data and information collected during`
  line `enrolment, all details of authentication performed, debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all`
  line `contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for such Unique`
  line `Identification Authority of India immediately before that day, for or in connection with the purpose of`
  line `the said Unique Identification Authority of India, shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into`
  line `or engaged to be done by, with or for, the Autho rity;`
  line `( c ) all sums of money due to the said Unique Identification Authority of India immediately before`
  line `that day shall be deemed to be due to the Authority; and`
  line `( d ) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against such Unique Identification Authority of India immediately before that day may be continued`
  line `or may be institut ed by or against the Authority.`
  line `23. Powers and functions of Authority. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall develop the policy, procedure and`
  line `systems fo r issuing Aadhaar numbers to individuals and perform authentication thereof under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to sub - section ( 1 ), the powers and functions of the Authority, inter alia,`
  line `include —`
  line `( a ) specifying, by regulations, demographic information and biometric information required for`
  line `enrolment and the processes for collection and verification thereof;`
  line `( b ) collecting demographic information and biometric information from any individual seeking an`
  line `Aadhaar number in such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( c ) appointing of one or more entities to operate the Central Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( d ) generating and assigning Aadhaar numbers to individuals;`
  line `( e ) performing authentication of Aadhaar numbers;`
  line `( f ) maintaining and updating the informat ion of individuals in the Central Identities Data`
  line `Repository in such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( g ) omitting and deactivating of an Aadhaar number and information relating thereto in such`
  line `manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( h ) speci fying the manner of use of Aadhaar numbers for the purposes of providing or availing of`
  line `various subsidies, benefits, services and other purposes for which Aadhaar numbers may be used;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 10, for section 21 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `( i ) specifying, by regulations, the terms and conditions for appointment of Registrars, enrolling`
  line `agencies and service providers and revocation of appointments thereof;`
  line `( j ) establishing, operating and maintaining of the Central Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( k ) sharing, in such manner as may be specified by regulations, the info rmation of Aadhaar`
  line `number holders, subject to the provisions of this Act;`
  line `( l ) calling for information and records, conducting inspections, inquiries and audit of the`
  line `operations for the purposes of this Act of the Central Identities Data Repository, Registr ars, enrolling`
  line `agencies and other agencies appointed under this Act;`
  line `( m ) specifying, by regulations, various processes relating to data management, security protocols`
  line `and other technology safeguards under this Act;`
  line `( n ) specifying, by regulations, the condi tions and procedures for issuance of new Aadhaar number`
  line `to existing Aadhaar number holder;`
  line `( o ) levying and collecting the fees or authorising the Registrars, enrolling agencies or other`
  line `service providers to collect such fees for the services provided by th em under this Act in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by regulations;`
  line `( p ) appointing such committees as may be necessary to assist the Authority in discharge of its`
  line `functions for the purposes of this Act;`
  line `( q ) promoting research and development for advancement in biometrics and related areas,`
  line `including usage of Aadhaar numbers through appropriate mechanisms;`
  line `( r ) evolving of, and specifying, by regulations, policies and practices for Registrars, enrolling`
  line `agencies and other service providers;`
  line `( s ) sett ing up facilitation centres and grievance redressal mechanism for redressal of grievances of`
  line `individuals, Registrars, enrolling agencies and other service providers;`
  line `( t ) such other powers and functions as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) The Authority may, —`
  line `( a ) enter into Memorandum of Understanding or agreement, as the case may be, with the Central`
  line `Government or State Governments or Union territories or other agencies for the purpose of`
  line `performing any of the functions in relation to collecting, storing, securing or processing of`
  line `information or delivery of Aadhaar numbers to individuals or performing authentication;`
  line `( b ) by notification, appoint such number of Registrars, engage and authorise such agencies to`
  line `collect, store, secure, process information or do authen tication or perform such other functions in`
  line `relation thereto,`
  line `as may be necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 4 ) The Authority may engage such consultants, advisors and other persons as may be required for`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions under this Act on such allowances or remuneration and terms and`
  line `conditions a s may be specified by contract.`
  line `1 [ 23A. Power of Authority to issue directions. — ( 1 ) The Authority may for the discharge of its`
  line `functions under this Act, or any rules or regulations made there under, by order, issue such directions`
  line `from time to time to any entity in the Aadhaar ecosystem, as it may consider necessary.`
  line `( 2 ) Every direction issued under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be complied with by the entity in the Aadhaar`
  line `ecosystem to whom such dire ction is issued.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 11 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-14
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Page 14`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `G RANTS, A CCOUNTS AND A UDIT AND A NNUAL R EPORT`
  line `24. Grants by Central Government. — The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Authority, grants of such sums of money as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit for being utilise d for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `1 [ 25. Fund. — ( 1 ) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the Unique Identification Authority of`
  line `India Fund and there shall be credited thereto —`
  line `( a ) all grants, fees and charges received by the Authority under this Act; and`
  line `( b ) all sums received by the Authority from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The Fund shall be applied for meeting —`
  line `( a ) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and members and administrative`
  line `expenses including the salaries, allowances and pension payable to or in respect of officers and other`
  line `employees of the Authority; and`
  line `( b ) the expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act.]`
  line `26. Accounts and audit. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and pr epare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India.`
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor - General`
  line `of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with`
  line `such audit shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor - General.`
  line `( 3 ) The Comptroller and Auditor - General of India and any pers on appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit the accounts of the Authority under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor - General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts, and in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers, and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Authority.`
  line `( 4 ) The accounts of the Authority, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the Authority and the Central Gove rnment shall cause the audit`
  line `report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
  line `27. Returns and annual report, etc. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall furnish to the Central Government at`
  line `such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct,`
  line `such returns and statements and particulars in regard to any matter under the jurisdiction of the Authority,`
  line `as the Central Government may from time to time require.`
  line `( 2 ) The Authority shall prep are, once in every year, and in such form and manner and at such time as`
  line `may be prescribed, an annual report giving —`
  line `( a ) a description of all the activities of the Authority for the previous years;`
  line `( b ) the annual accounts for the previous year; and`
  line `( c ) the programmes of work for coming year.`
  line `( 3 ) A copy of the report received under sub - section ( 2 ) shall be laid by the Central Government, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is received, b efore each House of Parliament.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 12, for section 25 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `P ROTECTIONOF I NFORMATION`
  line `28. Security and confidentiality of information. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall ensure the security of`
  line `identity information and authentication records of individuals.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Authority shall ensure confidentiality of identity`
  line `i nformation and authentication records of individuals.`
  line `( 3 ) The Authority shall take all necessary measures to ensure that the information in the possession or`
  line `control of the Authority, including information stored in the Central Identities Data Repository, is secured`
  line `and protected against access, use or disclosure not permitted under this Act or regulations made`
  line `thereunder, and against accidental or intentional destruction, loss or damage.`
  line `( 4 ) Without prejudice to sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Authority shall —`
  line `( a ) adopt and implement appropriate technical and organisational security measures;`
  line `( b ) ensure that the agencies, consultants, advisors or other persons appointed or engaged for`
  line `performing any function of the Authority under this Act, have in place appropriate technical and`
  line `organisational security measures for the information; and`
  line `( c ) ensure that the agreements or arrangements entered into with such agencies, consultants,`
  line `advisors or other persons, impose obligations equivalent to those imposed on th e Authority under this`
  line `Act, and require such agencies, consultants, advisors and other persons to act only on instructions`
  line `from the Authority.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, and save as`
  line `otherwise provid ed in this Act, the Authority or any of its officers or other employees or any agency that`
  line `maintains the Central Identities Data Repository shall not, whether during his service or thereafter, reveal`
  line `any information stored in the Central Identities Data Re pository or authentication record to anyone:`
  line `Provided that an Aadhaar number holder may request the Authority to provide access to his identity`
  line `information excluding his core biometric information in such manner as m ay be specified by regulations.`
  line `29. Rest riction on sharing information. — ( 1 ) No core biometric information, collected or created`
  line `under this Act, shall be —`
  line `( a ) shared with anyone for any reason whatsoever; or`
  line `( b ) used for any purpose other than generation of Aadhaar numbers and authentication under this`
  line Act.
  line `( 2 ) The identity information, other than core biometric information, collected or created under this`
  line `Act may be shared only in accordance with the provisions of this Act and in such man ner as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) No identity information available with a requesting entity or offline verification - seeking entity`
  line `shall be —`
  line `( a ) used for any purpose, other than the purposes informed in writing to the individual at the time`
  line `of submitting any information for authentication or offline verification; or`
  line `( b ) disclosed for any purpose, other than purposes informed in writing to the individual at the time`
  line `of submitting any information for authentication or offline verification:`
  line `Provided that the purposes under clauses ( a ) and ( b ) shall be in clear and precise language`
  line `understandable to the individual.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 13, for sub - section (3) (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
