  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `( 4 ) No Aadhaar number 1 [, demographic information or photograph] collected or created under this`
  line `Act in respect of an Aadhaar number holder shall be published, displayed or posted publicly, except for`
  line `the purposes as m ay be specified by regulations.`
  line `30. Biometric information deemed to be sensitive personal information. — The biometric`
  line `information collected and stored in electronic form, in accordance with this Act and regulations made`
  line `thereunder, shall be deemed to be “ electronic record ” and “ sensitive personal data or information ”, and`
  line `the provisions contained in the Info rmation Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) and the rules made`
  line `thereunder shall apply to such information, in addition to, and to the extent not in derogation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expressions —`
  line `( a ) “ electronic form ” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( r ) of sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line `( b ) “ electronic record ” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( t ) of sub - section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line `( c ) “ sensitive personal data or information ” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause ( iii ) of the Explanation to section 43A of the Information Tec hnology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).`
  line `31. Alteration of demographic information or biomet ric information. — ( 1 ) In case any`
  line `demographic information of an Aadhaar number holder is found incorrect or changes subsequently, the`
  line `Aadhaar number holder shall request the Authority to alter such demographic information in his record in`
  line `the Central Identities Data Repository in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line `( 2 ) In case any biometric information of Aadhaar number holder is lost or changes subsequently for`
  line `any reason, the Aadhaar number holder shall request the Authority to make neces sary alteration in his`
  line `record in the Central Identities Data Repository in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line `( 3 ) On receipt of any request under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ), the Authority may, if it is`
  line `satisfied, make such alteration a s may be required in the record relating to such Aadhaar number holder`
  line `and intimate such alteration to the concerned Aadhaar number holder.`
  line `( 4 ) No identity information in the Central Identities Data Repository shall be altered except in the`
  line `manner provided in this Act or r egulations made in this behalf.`
  line `32. Access to own information and records of requests for authentication. — ( 1 ) The Authority`
  line `shall maintain authentication records in such manner and for such period as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line `( 2 ) Ev ery Aadhaar number holder shall be entitled to obtain his authentication record in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
  line `( 3 ) The Authority shall not, either by itself or through any entity under its control, collect, keep or`
  line `maintain any informat ion about the purpose of authentication.`
  line `33. Disclosure of information in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Nothing contained in sub - section ( 2 ) or`
  line `sub - section ( 5 ) of section 28 or sub - section ( 2 ) of section 29 shall apply in respect of any disclosure of`
  line `information, including identity information or authentication records, made pursuant to an order of a court`
  line `not inferior to that of a 2 [Judge of a High Court]:`
  line `Provided that no order by the court under this sub - section shall be made without giving an`
  line `opportunity of hearing to the Authority 3 [ and the concerned Aadhaar number holder ].`
  line `3 [Provided further that the core biometric information shall not be disclosed under this sub - section.]`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub - section ( 2 ) or sub - section ( 5 ) of section 28 and clause ( b ) of sub - section`
  line `( 1 ), sub - section ( 2 ) or sub - section ( 3 ) of section 29 shall apply in respect of any disclosure of information,`
  line `including identity information or authentication reco rds, made in the interest of national security in`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 13, for “or core biometric information” (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for “District Judge” (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 14, ibid, (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
