  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `pursuance of a direction of an officer not below the rank of 1 [ Secretary ] to the Government of India`
  line `specially authorised in this behalf by an order of the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that every direction issued under this sub - section, shall be reviewed by an Oversight`
  line `Committee consisting of the Cabinet Secretary and the Secretaries to the Government of India in the`
  line `Department of Legal Affairs and the Department of Electronics and Information Technology, b efore it`
  line `takes effect:`
  line `Provided further that any direction issued under this sub - section shall be valid for a period of three`
  line `months from the date of its issue, which may be extended for a further period of three months after the`
  line `rev iew by the Oversight Co mmittee.`
  line `2 [C HAPTER VIA`
  line `C IVIL PENALTIES`
  line `33A. Penalty for failure to comply with provisions of this Act, rules, regulations and`
  line `directions. — ( 1 ) Where an entity in the Aadhaar ecosystem fails to comply with the provision of this Act,`
  line `the rules or regulations made there under or directions issued by the Authority under section 23A, or fails`
  line `to furnish any information, document, or return of report required by the Authority, such entity shall be`
  line `liable to a civil penalty which may extend to one crore rupees for each contravention and in case of a`
  line `continuing failure, with additional penalty which may extend to ten lakh rupees for every day during`
  line `which the failure continues after the first contravention.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount of any penalty imposed under this section, if not paid, may be recovered as if it were`
  line `an arrear of land revenue.`
  line `33B. Power to adjudicate. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of adjudication under section 33A and imposing a`
  line `penalty there under, the Authority shall appoint an officer of the Authority, who is not below the rank of a`
  line `Joint Secretary to the Government of India and possessing such qualification and experience as may be`
  line `prescribed, to be an Adjudicating Officer for holding an inquiry in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) No inquiry under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be initiated except by a complaint made by the Authority.`
  line `( 3 ) While holding an inquiry, the Adjudicating Officer shall —`
  line `( a ) provide the entity in the Aadhaar ecosystem against whom complaint is made, an opportunity of`
  line `being heard;`
  line `( b ) have the power to summon and enforce the attendance of any person acquainted with the facts`
  line `and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any document which, in the opinion of`
  line `the Adjudicating Officer, may be useful for or relevant to the s ubject matter of the inquiry.`
  line `( 4 ) If the Adjudicating Officer, on such inquiry, is satisfied that the entity in the Aadhaar ecosystem`
  line `has failed to comply with any provision of this Act or the rules or regulations made there under or`
  line `directions issued by t he Authority under section 23A, or has failed to furnish any information, document,`
  line `or return of report required by the Authority, the Adjudicating Officer may, by order, impose such penalty`
  line `under section 33A as he thinks fit.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 14, for “ Joint Secretary” (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 15, ibid, (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
