  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `33C. Appeals to Appellate Tri bunal. — ( 1 ) The Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal`
  line `established under section 14 of the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997), shall`
  line `be Appellate Tribunal for the purposes of hearing appeals against the decision of the Adjudicating Officer`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) A person or entity in the Aadhaar ecosystem aggrieved by an order of the Adjudicating Officer`
  line `under section 33B, may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal within a period of forty - five days from`
  line `the date of rec eipt of the order appealed against, in such form and manner and accompanied with such fee`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty - five days if it is satisfied that ther e was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line `( 3 ) On receipt of an appeal under sub - section ( 2 ), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties`
  line `to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line `( 4 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal and`
  line `to the Adjudicating Officer.`
  line `( 5 ) Any appeal filed under sub - section ( 2 ) shall be deal t with by the Appellate Tribunal as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and every endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal within six`
  line `months from the date on which it is presented to it.`
  line `( 6 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, for the purpose of deciding an ap peal before it, call for the records`
  line `relevant to disposing of such appeal and make such orders as it thinks fit.`
  line `33D. Procedure and powers of the Appellate Tribunal. — The provisions of sections 14 - I to 14K`
  line `(both inclusive), 16 and 17 of the Telecom Regulat ory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997) shall,`
  line `mutatis mutandis, apply to the Appellate Tribunal in the discharge of its functions under this Act, as they`
  line `apply to it in the discharge of its functions under that Act.`
  line `33E. Appeal to Supreme Court of India. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or in any other law for the time being in force, an appeal shall lie`
  line `against any order, not being an interlocutory order, of the Appellate Tribunal to the Suprem e Court on any`
  line `substantial question of law arising out of such order.`
  line `( 2 ) No appeal shall lie against any decision or order made by the Appellate Tribunal which the parties`
  line `have consented to.`
  line `( 3 ) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of forty - five days from the date`
  line `of the decision or order appealed against:`
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty - five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient caus e for not filing it within that period.`
  line `33F. Civil court not to have jurisdiction. — No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit`
  line `or proceeding in respect of any matter which an Adjudicating Officer appointed under this Act or the`
  line `Appellate T ribunal is empowered, by or under this Act to determine, and no injunction shall be granted by`
  line `any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power`
  line `conferred by or under this Act. ]`
