  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `O FFENCESAND P ENALTIES`
  line `34. Penalty for impersonation at time of enrolment. — Whoever impersonates or attempts to`
  line `impersonate another person, whether dead or alive, real or imaginary, by providing any false demographic`
  line `information or biometric information, shall be punisha ble with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or with a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with both.`
  line `35. Penalty for impersonation of Aadhaar number holder by changing demographic`
  line `information or biometric information. — Whoev er, with the intention of causing harm or mischief to an`
  line `Aadhaar number holder, or with the intention of appropriating the identity of an Aadhaar number holder`
  line `changes or attempts to change any demographic information or biometric information of an Aadhaar`
  line `number holder by impersonating or attempting to impersonate another person, dead or alive, real or`
  line `imaginary, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and shall`
  line `also be liable to a fine which may extend to ten thous and rupees.`
  line `36. Penalty for impersonation. — Whoever, not being authorised to collect identity information`
  line `under the provisions of this Act, by words, conduct or demeanour pretends that he is authorised to do so,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with a fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees or, in the case of a company, with a fine which may extend t o one lakh`
  line `rupees or with both.`
  line `37. Penalty for d isclosing identity information. — Whoever, intentionally discloses, transmits,`
  line `copies or otherwise disseminates any identity information collected in the course of enrolment or`
  line `authentication to any person not authorised under this Act or regulations made t hereunder or in`
  line `contravention of any agreement or arrangement entered into pursuant to the provisions of this Act, shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with a fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees or, i n the case of a company, with a fine which may extend t o one lakh`
  line `rupees or with both.`
  line `38. Penalty for unauthorised access to the Central Identities Data Repository. — Whoever, not`
  line `being authorised by the Authority, intentionally, —`
  line `( a ) accesses or secures access to the Central Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( b ) downloads, copies or extracts any data from the Central Identities Data Repository or stored in`
  line `any removable storage medium;`
  line `( c ) introduces or causes to be introduced any virus or other computer contam inant in the Central`
  line `Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( d ) damages or causes to be damaged the data in the Central Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( e ) disrupts or causes disruption of the access to the Central Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( f ) denies or causes a denia l of access to any person who is authorised to access the Central`
  line `Identities Data Repository;`
  line `( g ) reveals any information in contravention of sub - section (5) of section 28, or shares, uses or`
  line `displays information in contravention of section 29 or assists a ny person in any of the aforementioned`
  line acts;
  line `( h ) destroys, deletes or alters any information stored in any removable storage media or in the`
  line `Central Identities Data Repository or diminishes its value or utility or affects it injuriously by any`
  line `means; or`
  line `( i ) steals, conceals, destroys or alters or causes any person to steal, conceal, destroy or alter any`
  line `computer source code used by the Authority with an intention to cause damage,`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
