  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to 1 [ten years] and shall also`
  line `be liable to a fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expressions “ computer contaminant ”,`
  line `“ computer virus ” and “ damage ” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to t hem in the`
  line `Explanation to section 43 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000), and the expression`
  line `“ computer source code ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to section 65 of the`
  line `said Act.`
  line `39. Penalty for tampering with data in Central Identities Data Repository. — Whoever, not being`
  line `authorised by the Authority, uses or tampers with the data in the Central Identities Data Repository or in`
  line `any removable storage medium with the intent of modifying information relating to Aadhaar number`
  line `holder or discovering any information thereof, shall be punish able with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to 2 [ t en years ] and shall also be liable to a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
  line `3 [ 40. Penalty for unauthorised use by requesting entity or offline verification - seeking entity. —`
  line `Whoever, — ( a ) being a requesting entity, uses the identity information of an individual in`
  line `contravention of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 8; or`
  line `( b ) being an offline verification - seeking entity, uses the identity information of an individual in`
  line `contravention of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 8A, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to three years or with a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or, in the case of a`
  line `company, with a fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with both.]`
  line `41. Penalty for non - compliance with intimation requirements. — Whoever, being an enrolling`
  line `agency or a requesting entity, fails to comply with the requirements of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3 or sub -`
  line `section ( 3 ) of section 8, shall be 4 [ liable to penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees, or in the case of`
  line `a company, with penalty which may extend to ten lakh rupees ].`
  line `42. General penalty. — Whoever commits an offence under this Act or any rules or regulations made`
  line `thereunder for which no specific penalty is provided elsewhere than this section, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to 5 [three year ] or with a fine w hich may extend to`
  line `twenty - five thousand rupees or, in the case of a company, with a fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line `43. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, ever y person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `c onnivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section —`
  line `( a ) “ company ” means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line `( b ) “ director ”, in relation to a fir m, means a partner in the firm.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 16 for “three years” (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for section 40 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 30 - 11 - 2023).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 19, for “One year” (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `44. Act to apply for offence or contravention committed outside India. — ( 1 ) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub - section ( 2 ), the provisions of this Act shall apply also to any offence or contravention`
  line `committed outside India by any person, irrespective o f his nationality.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub - section ( 1 ), the provisions of this Act shall apply to any offence or`
  line `contravention committed outside India by any person, if the act or conduct constituting the offence or`
  line `contravention involves any data in the Central Identiti es Data Repository.`
  line `45. Power to investigate offences. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a police officer not below the rank of Inspector of Police shall investig ate`
  line `any offence unde r this Act.`
  line `46. Penalties not to interfere with other punishments. — No penalty imposed under this Act shall`
  line `prevent the imposition of any other penalty or punishment under any other l aw for the time being in force.`
  line `47. Cognizance of offences. — ( 1 ) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act, save on a complaint made by the Authority or any officer or person authorised by it.`
  line `1 [Provided that the court may, on a complaint made by an Aadhaar number holder or individual tak e`
  line `cognizance of any offence punishable under section 34 or 35 or 36 or 37 or 40 or section 41.]`
  line `( 2 ) No court inferior to that of a Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or a Chief Judicial Magistrate shall try`
  line `any off ence punishable under this Act.`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M I SCELLANEOUS`
  line `48. Power of Central Government to supersede Authority. — ( 1 ) If, at any time, the Central`
  line `Government is of the opinion, —`
  line `( a ) that, on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Authority, it is unable to discharge`
  line `the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line `( b ) that the Authority has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction giv en by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the duties`
  line `imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the financial`
  line `position of the Authority or the administration of the Authority has suffered; or`
  line `( c ) that a public emergency exists,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, supersede the Authority for such period, not exceeding six`
  line `months, as may be specified in the notification and appoint a person or persons as the President may`
  line `direct to exercise powers and discharge functions under this Act:`
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Authority to make representations against the propo sed supersession and shall consider`
  line `the representations, if any, of the Authority.`
  line `( 2 ) Upon the publication of a notification under sub - section ( 1 ), superseding the Authority, —`
  line `( a ) the Chairperson and other Members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their`
  line `offices as such;`
  line `( b ) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub - section ( 3 ), be exercised and discharged by the person or persons referred to in sub - section`
  line `( 1 ); and`
  line `( c ) all properties owned or controlled by the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub - section ( 3 ), vest in the Central Government.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 20 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `( 3 ) On or befor e the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government shall reconstitute the Authority by a fresh appointment of its`
  line `Chairperson and other Members and in such case any person who h ad vacated his office under clause ( a )`
  line `of sub - section ( 2 ) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for reappointment.`
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government shall cause a copy of the notification issued under sub - section ( 1 ) and a`
  line `full report of any action taken under t his section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament at the earliest.`
  line `49. Members, officers, etc., to be public servants. — The Chairperson, Members, officers and other`
  line `employees of the Authority shall be deeme d, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860).`
  line `50. Power of Central Government to issue directions. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Authority shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act be bound by such directions on questions of po licy, as the Central Government may give,`
  line `in writing to it, from time to time:`
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub - section:`
  line `Provided further tha t nothing in this section shall empower the Central Government to issue`
  line `directions pertaining to technical or administrative matters undertaken by the Authority.`
  line `( 2 ) The decision of the Central Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be final.`
  line `1 [ 50A. Exemption from tax on income. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income - tax`
  line `Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) or any other enactment for the time being in force relating to tax on income,`
  line `profits or gains, the Authority shall not be liable to pay income - tax or any other tax in respect of its`
  line `income, profits or gains.]`
  line `51. Delegation. — The Authority may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any`
  line `2 [Member or officer] of the Authority or any other person, subjec t to such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act (except the power under sectio n 54)`
  line `as it may deem necessary.`
  line `52. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the Authority or the Chairperson or any Member or any officer, or`
  line `other employees of the Authority for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this Act or the rule or regulati on made thereunder.`
  line `53. Power of Central Government to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the form and manner in which and the authority before whom the oath of office and of secrecy`
  line `is to be subscribed by the Chairperson and Members under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 14;`
  line `3 [( aa ) the purpose for which the requesting entity may be allowed by the Authority to perform`
  line `authentication under sub - clause ( ii ) of clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 4 ) of section 4;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 21 (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for “Member, officer” (w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019)`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 23, ibid, ( w.e.f. 25 - 7 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
