  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `( x ) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified, or in respect of which provision`
  line `is to be or may be made by regulations.`
  line `55. Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament. — Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may b e comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or`
  line `bo th the Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
  line `56. Application of other laws not barred. — The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, any other l aw for the time being in force.`
  line `57. Act not to prevent use of Aadhaar number for other purposes under law. — Omitted by the`
  line `Aadhaar and Other Laws ( Amendment ) Act 2019 ( Act 14 of 2019), s. 25 ( w.e.f. 25 - 0 7 - 2019 )`
  line `58. Power to remove difficulties. — ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, b efore each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line `59. Savings. — Anything done or any action taken by the Central Government under the Resolution of`
  line `the Government of India, Planning Commission bearing notification number A - 43011/02/2009 - Admin. I,`
  line `dated the 28th January, 2009, or by the Department of Electronics and Information Technology under the`
  line `Cabinet Secretariat Notification bearing notification number S.O.2492 ( E ), dated the 12th September,`
  line `2015, as the case may be, shall be deemed to have b een validl y done or taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
